{"ticker": "SHIELD_AI", "company": "Shield AI", "weight_sum": 4.92, "etfs": ["ARKVX", "ARKUX", "ARKSX"], "is_private": true, "query": "\"Shield AI\" -is:retweet min_faves:10 since:2026-04-29 until:2026-05-01", "n_fetched": 2, "n_kept": 2, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2049519990794011090", "url": "https://x.com/shieldaitech/status/2049519990794011090", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/shieldaitech/status/2049519990794011090", "text": "A new chapter in New Delhi!\n\nThis week, our President and Co-Founder @rtsengusa and retired U.S. Navy Admiral John Aquilino, former @INDOPACOM commander and member of our Defense Advisory Board, joined Managing Director Sarjan Shah for the official opening of Shield AI's New Delhi office and met with the Indian Ministry of Defence.\n\nShield AI India is now live as a wholly owned subsidiary supporting software integration, engineering, and autonomy development. The New Delhi office is open with a second location in Bengaluru opening this summer.\n\n\"Being a strong partner means being present and working alongside our customers. With our New Delhi office, and with our plans to expand soon in Bengaluru as well, we are strengthening our ability to support India's autonomy priorities and partner on systems that can be built, deployed, and sustained within the country, while growing a pipeline of Indian engineers and developers who can build and evolve mission autonomy on Indian terms.\" \u2014 Sarjan Shah\n\nFull press release in comments.\n\nAutonomy for the world. The greatest victory requires no war.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 8, "replyCount": 4, "likeCount": 44, "quoteCount": 3, "viewCount": 2696, "createdAt": "Wed Apr 29 16:03:38 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 7, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049519990794011090", "displayTextRange": [0, 275], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "shieldaitech"